    "updated_at": "2014-03-03T21:12:17Z",
    "body": "Related to https://github.com/atom/atom-shell/issues/193 - @zcbenz - I see from the api docs you linked to that the default for `node-integration` is `all`.  I am not 100% clear on when/how often iframes are used within the main Atom UI, but I would think that wanting Node integration within an iframe is the exception rather than the rule. If so, could we have the default for iframe be `manual-enable-iframe` so that developers must explicitly specify their desire to execute privileged Node code from within an iframe (can we even come up with a use case for this?).\n"
  },
