    "updated_at": "2014-03-03T21:33:08Z",
    "body": "@probablycorey - I just tried this out.  Changing the line you mentioned does seem to remove the Node integration in an iframe (trivially validate by trying to access the `process` object).  But, I was still able to do: `window.parent.process.exit()`. So, it would be cool if we could figure out how/if it is possible to prevent cross-origin iframe navigation. We can possibly go down the path of the hack node-webkit used, but it would be neat if we could leverage the built-in `sandbox` stuff. But, in order for that to have any chance of working we need to figure out #193.\n"
  }
